doWork

java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> doWork(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> workerMap)
CONFEXTENSION: You only need to return null. You became a HashMap with "additionalData" (HashMap), "rootFolder" (File) and "name" (String)
CONTENTEXTENSION: you need to return a HashMap with key "content" and became a HashMap with "content".

getAdditionlInfo

java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getAdditionlInfo(java.lang.String[] basicInfo)
Returns additional infos if return not null. basicInfo is a String-Array. It contains:
basicInfo[0] = whitespaces in foldergenconf
basicInfo[1] = all behind the filemarker
